# OpenCV Computer Vision Flask App

A simple Flask web application for real-time computer vision tasks using OpenCV. Features include:

- Live video streaming from your webcam
- Canny edge detection
- Face detection and face blurring
- Capture and save images from any video feed
- Downsample captured images
- Modern, user-friendly web interface

## Requirements
- Python 3.8+
- Flask
- OpenCV (`opencv-python`)
- flask-cors

## Usage
1. Start the Flask server: `python main.py`
2. Open `index.html` in your browser
3. Click "Start Live Video" to begin
4. Use the buttons to apply filters, capture images, and more

## Notes
- Make sure your webcam is connected
- Place `haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml` in the project directory for face detection
- Captured images are saved in the `capture` folder